# Code style essentials

- Match the style of the surrounding code in the same module/file.
- Do not delete existing comments unless they are demonstrably wrong or obsolete.
- Do not add trivial narration comments (`// increment`, `// init viewmodel`, `// return result`).
- Add a comment only for non-obvious intent, trade-offs, invariants, or constraints the code itself cannot convey, comments should be clean, compact and precise, not bloated.
- Code comments in English (this is a public repo). User-facing strings are localized (ru/en/zh) in resource files — never hardcoded in code.
- No emojis in code, commit messages, or PR descriptions.
- Prefer expressive names and small, focused functions over comments.
- Never commit secrets, tokens, API keys, signing keystores, `local.properties`, or service-account JSON. Keep them out of VCS and out of committed `BuildConfig` source.
